  "title": "Customer Project Manager (Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Serve as the primary point of contact for customers, ensuring clear communication throughout project lifecycles.</li><li>Involve in all projects requiring engineering and development support to fulfill customer orders.</li><li>Work closely with engineering teams to ensure project specifications and requirements are met.</li><li>Coordinate project timelines, budgets, and resources to ensure on-time delivery and customer satisfaction.</li><li>Identify and troubleshoot any technical issues that arise during project execution.</li><li>Prepare and present project updates and reports to stakeholders, ensuring transparency and alignment.</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to enhance product quality and meet customer expectations.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Diploma or Degree in Mechanical, Electrical, or Mechatronic Engineering.</li><li>Proven experience in semiconductor industry.</li><li>Strong project management and organizational skills.</li><li>Excellent communication and interpersonal abilities.</li><li>Ability to work effectively in a fast-paced and dynamic environment.</li></ul><p>If interested, please submit your application to cvs@jdawms.com with your expected salary and resume.</p><p>We regret that only short-listed candidates will be contacted shortly. By submitting your application or resume, you agree to the collection, use, retention, and sharing of your personal information with potential employers for their assessment.</p><p>JDA WMS Pte Ltd | EA Personnel: Pham Thi Tuyet Mai </p><p>EA License No: 23S1595 | EA Registration No: R25127838</p>",
